FBIS4-31248 "dreeu110_i_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Senior Humanitarian Aid Official To Be Tried Senior Humanitarian Aid Official To Be Tried LD0706223694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706223694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] The main hearing at the trial of Dusko Tomic, secretary-general of the 1st Children's Embassy, will begin on 11 June, Bosnia-Herzegovina Press reports. It is suspected that Tomic has cooperated with the aggressor and he is considered the one most guilty for the inadequate organization of a convoy carrying food from Macedonia [Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], which eventually ended up in the aggressor's hands in Pale.
